At 07:58 AM 08/09/2002, you wrote:
>   With the new switch in, now it will only crank if you push the key in 
> toward the steering column while cranking it.  What gives??  It's as if 
> the lock portion is now worn, although the lock that's in there is a 
> replacement one...(don't know how long it's been there).  Does anyone 
> have any thoughts as to how to rectify this?  tia, Greg


I replaced today the same elec. switch contacts on one I had replaced less 
than 2 years ago. I think you got a new switch that is garbage out of the 
box. Just poor contact from bad tolerances in manufacture. You can prove 
this fault with an ohm meter. 

